Procedure Note
Resident: Dr. Smith
Attending: Dr. Jones
Diagnosis: Esophageal Ca with TE fistula.
Procedure Steps:
1. Time out.
2. LMA placed. Flex bronch showed LMS tumor and fistula.
3. Switched to Rigid Bronch (12mm).
4. Biopsied mass. APC used for hemostasis and debulking.
5. Y-Stent (Silicone) loaded and deployed via rigid scope.
6. Flexible check confirmed position covering fistula.
Complications: Tongue laceration.
